Czech Equities Rise From Three-Month Low as NWR, Pegas Advance

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-03-17T10:20:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/czech-equities-rise-from-three-month-low-as-nwr-pegas-advance.html
The Czech Republic’s main equity
index advanced from its lowest in almost three months, led
higher by  New World Resources NV (NWR) ,  Telefonica O2 Czech Republic
AS (SPTT)  and  Pegas Nonwovens SA. (PEGAS)   The PX gauge jumped as much as 0.4 percent and traded up
0.2 percent at 1,203.6 as of 11 a.m. in Prague. The index of 15
companies lost 1.3 percent in the previous three sessions to the
lowest level since Dec. 20 at yesterday’s close.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  